content.description: This climbs the left bolt line on this cliff.  The only line on the face--The other is on the arete.  The climb is a nice climb with a nasty thorn bush 1/3 the way up.  The crux is getting beyond the ledge at 2/3's height.  The rock is smooth and slippery, and the holds up top are thin.  Very enjoyable, with good pro.  The roof protects wonderfully.
content.protection: 2 bolts atop for the anchors. Five draws for the climb.

content.description: This climbs the arete with bolts.  Another nice climb with water polished rock.  Don't use the gully, just the arete.  A nice summer evening climb.  AKA Spring Feed
content.protection: 2 bolts atop, and I believe 7? draws needed for the rest of the climb.  I brought a med cam for a tricky bulge that I felt exposed on, but not neccesary.

content.description: This climbs up the recessed area of the face, it angles left along a nice finger crack and then commences to fight its way to the top through vegetation, and bad rock.  It's only saving grace is the nice finger crack
content.protection: 2 bolts are the anchors up top.  Medium and small gear protects the lead.
